1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 24

2
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:33,920
Happy New Year.

3
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:34,510
Happy New Year.

4
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,040
Eat. I'm starving.

5
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:38,950
Come on. Eat.

6
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:47,200
Um...

7
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,070
Well...

8
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,200
You guys eat first.

9
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,200
I have to go downstairs.

10
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,710
Isn't someone watching downstairs?

11
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:53,400
No.

12
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,040
According to the schedule,

13
00:01:55,310 --> 00:01:56,070
I should be

14
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,920
working right now.

15
00:01:58,590 --> 00:01:59,790
You young people eat first.

16
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,430
I'll eat

17
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:02,790
when my shift ends.

18
00:02:03,350 --> 00:02:03,920
Wait.

19
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:05,790
Gao Xiang,

20
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:06,480
tell him.

21
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:11,840
Mr. He,

22
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:12,910
it's like this.

23
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,870
Based on your performance,

24
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:17,430
the board of directors

25
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,190
decided

26
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:19,800
to raise

27
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:21,430
your salary.

28
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:23,400
What?

29
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:25,590
Raise my salary?

30
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,310
I've earned quite a lot.

31
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:30,870
You've contributed a lot too.

32
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:32,960
Especially since you
volunteered for the night shift.

33
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,710
You deserve a raise.

34
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,590
You've taken care of
my food and lodging.

35
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:39,000
My illness is cured.

36
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,000
I can't spend all the money I earn.

37
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,150
Um...

38
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,030
What more could I want?

39
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:47,190
Grandpa,

40
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,400
you're quite witty.

41
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:49,710
I learned it

42
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:50,840
from TV.

43
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,120
That's nice.

44
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,240
Then your salary increase

45
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,400
will be a little smaller.

46
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,030
What?

47
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,470
Just kidding.

48
00:02:58,910 --> 00:02:59,870
Your salary will increase.

49
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:00,750
Zhao Jun,

50
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,750
buy your grandpa

51
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:02,630
a bike.

52
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,310
Really?

53
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:05,910
You do a lot of work,

54
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,150
but you don't get enough exercise.

55
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,240
Riding a bike will

56
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,080
keep you healthy,

57
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,360
and you can even ride around town.

58
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,080
Wouldn't that be nice?

59
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:12,910
Great.

60
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:15,630
It would be so relaxing

61
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:16,560
to be able to ride

62
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,030
a bike in Shenzhen.

63
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,710
Sir,

64
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:40,000
don't look around.

65
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:40,910
Be careful.

66
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,630
I knew it was you.

67
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,710
You were

68
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,080
playing me!

69
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,960
Want to try this? It's better.

70
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,870
No.

71
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,080
I know your bike is nice and

72
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:05,680
expensive.

73
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,310
But I

74
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,030
still prefer mine.

75
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,190
I was thinking on the way here.

76
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,800
If I could have

77
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:14,030
afforded a bike like this as part

78
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,630
of your sisters' gifts back then,

79
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,560
they could have married richer men.

80
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,600
It's pointless to think about that now.

81
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,240
Keep exercising every day.

82
00:04:21,430 --> 00:04:22,430
But be careful.

83
00:04:22,430 --> 00:04:23,390
Don't get hurt.

84
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,390
Okay. Don't worry.

85
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,600
I'm feeling great now.

86
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:27,360
Look,

87
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,750
I'm dressed smartly.

88
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,190
My legs aren't shaking.

89
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:32,310
I'll exercise.

90
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,680
Bye.

91
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:34,870
Be careful.

92
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:36,720
You too.

93
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:50,750
Most workers have

94
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:51,600
returned to work,

95
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:53,070
over 90%.

96
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,270
Before the New Year,

97
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:55,160
Mr. Sun next door tried

98
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:56,160
to poach our staff.

99
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,240
But everyone

100
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,360
is quite loyal,

101
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,390
saying Ms. Fang

102
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:01,240
is a good person

103
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,630
and Juan is considerate.

104
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,480
So they're willing

105
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,800
to work for us.

106
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,600
Mr. Sun's poaching tactics

107
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,680
are pretty good.

108
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,950
Anyone willing to work for him

109
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,870
gets a 10% raise.

110
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,750
This rule is specifically

111
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:14,830
targeted at us.

112
00:05:15,310 --> 00:05:16,830
Damn it.

113
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,510
What did we do to offend him?

114
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,070
Beat us up

115
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,510
so he can expand his factory.

116
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,480
The bigger the factory,

117
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,630
the more valuable it is.

118
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:26,560
Zhao.

119
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,600
Ms. Fang,

120
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:29,480
actually,

121
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,480
my situation isn't very good.

122
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,870
One of our orders has already

123
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:35,310
fallen through.

124
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:36,560
Mr. Sun

125
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,480
snatched it.

126
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:38,800
The other order

127
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,310
isn't guaranteed either.

128
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:41,560
Here's what

129
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,360
I'm thinking.

130
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,560
I'm planning to fly to Shanghai

131
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,310
to talk to him face-to-face.

132
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:48,190
Great.

133
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,430
Good luck.

134
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:49,950
Okay.

135
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,270
Li?

136
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,360
My situation is okay.

137
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,720
But there's not much growth.

138
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:56,920
There's a slight increase,

139
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:58,830
but prices can't go up.

140
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,160
Mainly because we lack a brand.

141
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,950
Being a salesperson
means a lot of traveling.

142
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,680
Face-to-face communication

143
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,480
is often much more

144
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:07,600
effective than phone calls.

145
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,870
Back when Ms. Li and I

146
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,390
were clothing distributors,

147
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,430
we traveled all

148
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:12,480
over the country.

149
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:13,830
I've booked a ticket.

150
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:14,720
I'll go tomorrow.

151
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,600
I'll book the ticket now.

152
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:18,630
Alright then.

153
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:19,430
That's all.

154
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:31,360
Sales are sluggish right now.

155
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,870
There's a backlog of unsold inventory.

156
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:33,920
Wanzhi.

157
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,750
How about we

158
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:39,870
shut down two production lines?

159
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:41,680
From a

160
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,120
cost-saving perspective.

161
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,270
That's the only way.

162
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:03,390
Is there a supermarket?

163
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,510
Don't know.

164
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:06,240
Checkmate.

165
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,510
Where is the supermarket?

166
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,040
Turn right ahead.

167
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,070
Finally.

168
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:19,510
Shenxian Peak?

169
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,680
What a stupid name.

170
00:07:30,830 --> 00:07:31,720
Welcome.

171
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:38,830
What are you doing?

172
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,560
Nice look.

173
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:43,680
Shenzhen is awesome.

174
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,070
Why are you here?

175
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,390
Shenzhen is full

176
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,560
of tall buildings.

177
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,270
There are plenty of stylish places.

178
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,680
Why are you opening a supermarket

179
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,430
in this crappy place?

180
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,560
Shenxian Peak?

181
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,160
Haven't you had enough?

182
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:01,000
Zhao Kai,

183
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,430
why did you dye your hair?

184
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,510
Cool, right?

185
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,630
My girl chose this color.

186
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,600
I love her.

187
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,430
Jun.

188
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:13,720
Any customers?

189
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:15,560
He Yongwang?

190
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:19,870
Holy crap.

191
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,430
Judging from your state,

192
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,630
you don't need that coffin anymore.

193
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:25,430
My dad wasted money again.

194
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,680
You little shit.

195
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,000
What did you do to your hair?

196
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,800
Why can't you learn to be good?

197
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:32,750
Don't touch my hair.

198
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:34,390
You little shit.

199
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:34,870
Grandpa.

200
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:35,360
Brat.

201
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:35,750
Grandpa.

202
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:36,550
Go get the scissors.

203
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,750
I cut it all off.

204
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:38,790
Go.

205
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:39,200
Zhao Kai!

206
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,080
Don't mess up my hair.

207
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,200
Zhao Kai,

208
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,790
get up. Auntie is here.

209
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:54,630
You're Fang Wanzhi?

210
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:56,630
You were prettier

211
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:58,480
when you were little.

212
00:08:58,670 --> 00:08:59,480
Watch your mouth!

213
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,670
Get up!

214
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,720
Zhao Kai, right?

215
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,630
You're a much bigger jerk

216
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:16,000
now than you were when little.

217
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:18,960
Didn't your parents

218
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,150
arrange a job for you?

219
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,960
Why aren't you working?

220
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,480
Work?

221
00:09:24,790 --> 00:09:25,910
That guy's a swindler.

222
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,270
Zhao Dazhi and He Xiaoju

223
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:28,670
are both idiots.

224
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,790
I told them I wouldn't work.

225
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,790
They should've

226
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,750
given the money to me.

227
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,960
If they gave me

228
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:35,200
the money, I'd be a success.

229
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:37,630
Really, Auntie.

230
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:38,870
I have a knack for business.

231
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,270
Don't just give Zhao Jun money.

232
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:41,200
Invest some in me.

233
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,200
100,000?

234
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,630
80,000?

235
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:46,550
I promise...

236
00:09:46,550 --> 00:09:47,360
Get up!

237
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,270
Don't you trust me?

238
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,720
Fang Wanzhi, you...

239
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:54,960
What are you doing?

240
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:57,320
You've dirtied my shoes!

241
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:02,630
Where's Xiaoju?

242
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,360
She's sick.

243
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:05,720
The swindler

244
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,840
got all her money.

245
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:08,080
She can't take it.

246
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:09,720
Where's your dad?

247
00:10:09,910 --> 00:10:10,790
My dad got sick first.

248
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:12,510
He looks strong,

249
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,360
but he has a heart condition.

250
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,870
Your parents are sick.

251
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:17,150
Shouldn't you take care of them?

252
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:18,870
What are you doing in Shenzhen?

253
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,200
I'm useless there.

254
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,630
I need to make something of myself

255
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:23,390
to show them

256
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,790
that I can succeed without a job,

257
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,480
at least better than Jun can.

258
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,440
Making something of
myself requires money.

259
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,840
That's why I came to Shenzhen.

260
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,750
You're my aunt.

261
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:37,960
You have to support me.

262
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:38,790
And Zhao Jun,

263
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,510
you're a boss now.

264
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,480
Give me some money.

265
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:43,670
I'll pay you back double

266
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:44,630
when I'm successful.

267
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:55,870
What a brat.

268
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,600
Did you call your parents?

269
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:01,600
Yes.

270
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,200
They are indeed sick.

271
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:05,510
How did they get scammed?

272
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:07,550
Someone promised to find Zhao Kai a job,

273
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:08,630
telling them to wait

274
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:10,270
until after the New Year.

275
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,150
He came to my house

276
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,240
on the 13th to drink

277
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,960
and took some money.

278
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,840
He said he could fix it.

279
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:18,000
But after the 15th,

280
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:19,270
they couldn't find him.

281
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,270
Taking shortcuts

282
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,390
deserves to be scammed.

283
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:23,550
My parents didn't know

284
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,390
he came to Shenzhen.

285
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:26,630
Can you control him?

286
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,360
But I don't want to.

287
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:31,480
Call him down.

288
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,120
Auntie,

289
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,270
what will you do?

290
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,270
I'll make him work in the factory.

291
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,080
Make him do whatever's hard.

292
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,390
No, Auntie.

293
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,840
He'll cause trouble.

294
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:44,240
Well,

295
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,790
I'll have him work here.

296
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,790
You just said you didn't want him.

297
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:53,120
After all, he's my brother.

298
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,600
Call your dad.

299
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:02,910
Tell him to get Zhao Kai

300
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:03,750
when he gets better.

301
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,200
